A BUS crashed into a house in Phoenix, north of Durban on Wednesday, 23 June. According to Prem Balram from Reaction Unit South Africa, no injuries were reported at the scene of the accident. He said the bus crashed into a house on Canehaven Drive in Caneside in Phoenix in the early hours of the morning. “Reaction Unit South Africa members arrived on scene at 6.57am and found that the bus drove through the boundary wall and into the front of the house. The driver of the bus was the only occupant in the vehicle at the time,” said Balram. He said the homeowner was inside the house at the time of the incident but was not injured. KZN police spokeswoman Colonel Thembeka Mbele said they can confirm an accident occurred at Canehaven Drive in Phoenix. “An accident report was registered,” said Mbele.